2007-12-08  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* client.c, configure.c, default.c, guimap.c, guiobjects.c,
	netclient.c, paint.h, paintdata.c, painthud.c, xevent.c:

	Remove WINDOWSCALING define: scaleFactor option is always present
	in the client.

2007-03-29  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* configure.c, default.c, paintradar.c: New option showRadar,
	which can be used to turn off radar drawing. This can help in
	reducing client lag (drawing time).

2007-03-29  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* painthud.c: Hudradar changes: paint enemies in red and teammates
	in green. HUD Radar scale is decreased from 3 to 2.

2007-03-24  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* painthud.c: Fix bug where a HUD radar dot is painted on top
	of the ship.

2007-03-20  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* client.c, configure.c: Handle maxFPS option in a better
	way. Client now allows any value from 1 to 255, instead of trying
	to limit the range to [FPS/2,FPS], where FPS is the server's FPS
	(frames per second sent to client). Value of maxFPS is saved
	into config file (.xpilotrc)

2007-02-18  Kristian Söderblom <kps@users.sourceforge.net>

	* all: Initial revision. The client is a copy of the client in
	XPilot 4.5.4. All files from client and common directories are in
	the bloodspilot2-clients/src/client/454 directory. GNU autotools
	are used to configure and make instead of xmkmf and Imake.
